article.headline: Wagner 73, St. Francis, N.Y., 66
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Joey Mundweiler scored all of his 15 points in the first half to lead Wagner to a 73-66 win over St. Francis, N.Y., on Saturday. James Ulrich had 14 points for the Seahawks (5-11, 2-3 Northeast), Mark Porter added 12 points and Matt Vitale had 10. Marcus Williams had 15 points for the Terriers (3-15, 1-5), Robert Hines and Allan Sheppard scored 13 each and Jamaal Womack added 11. St. Francis took a 14-3 lead at 14:11, with Womack contributing a pair of 3-point shots. Behind Mundweiler's 12 points, the Seahawks used a 34-14 run to take a 37-28 lead at the break. Jamal Smith hit two layups as Seahawks scored six straight points to open the second half. St. Francis pulled within 68-66 with :59 remaining on a layup by Hines. The Terriers missed a chance to tie when Williams failed to convert two foul shots with :29 remaining. Wagner sealed the game from the foul line, making five free throws.
